{
  "stem": "4289.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "If she had a piece of bread, it was always cut evenly and distributed to her and to me.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I remember when we were hungry, both of us were crying.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "She said, children don't cry, go to sleep.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You'll forget that you're hungry.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just by selling all her furniture, her jewelery.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whatever was in the house was no more there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were probably the poorest family in Czestochowa.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He had means in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If he wouldn't drink, he was a very rich man.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I-- the time I joined the family, he owned a lot of property in Czestochowa.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He had carriages by the train station with people who worked for him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He had a carriage for a funeral, I remember, a black one.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And a white carriage for weddings.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He had a restaurant, a billiard place, and a laundromat.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But eventually with him drinking and drinking, he lost at all.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was very dangerous because Gestapo was always on the trains looking for Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were looking through our luggages, checking what we have.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And really, selling cigarettes was a no-no.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And one day we were caught, both of us, my mother and I, because when they asked whose luggage it is, my mother turned away.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I said, it's ours because I was a child.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we were both taken off from the train to the Gestapo right in Czestochowa.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were separated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I wasn't scared yet, because I didn't know why.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But my mother was really scared.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we were separated.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the man who interviewed me there, he had a big bureau with pictures with his own family pictures.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And he sat me across from him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he looked at me, did a few gestures, picked up the phone.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
